Clean build. The warning is just Three.js being large (~500 KB bundled, 130 KB
   gzipped) — normal and expected, not an error.

  ---
  The two corrections I made vs. the previous files:

  main.js ordering — I moved state.initGameState(gameState) to after
  starMap.init(), sidebar.init(), and ui.init(). The design's order puts it
  before those calls, but that means stateLoaded fires before the DOM elements
  exist and before starMap.pointsGeometry is built, so all three listeners would
   no-op. The reordering means all listeners fire with everything ready.

  index.html DOM — Added id="year-display", id="pause-overlay", id="sidebar",
  and id="event-log", which ui.init() and sidebar.init() look up by ID.

